==============================================================================
OUTPUT — STRUCTURED MARKDOWN PROSE (NOT JSON)
==============================================================================

Emit your analysis as markdown using the section headers below. Sections you
have nothing to put in MUST be omitted entirely (do not write "N/A" or
empty bullets — just leave the section out). Brevity is rewarded.

```
## Defender — Round {{ round }}

### Position
ONE paragraph. State, in plain language, how strongly you defend the leading
hypothesis on the available evidence. Examples of acceptable positions:

  - "I defend [diagnosis] with high confidence: case findings X, Y, Z all
    converge, and the must-not-miss list is closed."
  - "I partially defend [diagnosis]: it remains the most likely, but the
    workup gap on [alternative] leaves my confidence moderate."
  - "I cannot defend [diagnosis] on this evidence: case findings A and B fit
    [other diagnosis] better. Recommend the Reasoner re-rank."

### Evidence supporting the leading hypothesis
Bulleted list. Each bullet either:
  - Quotes/paraphrases a case finding ("3-day history of crushing substernal pain")
  - Cites retrieved evidence by source_location ("Stern p.169 — troponin LR+ 9.5 for NSTEMI")
Skip this section entirely if you have no support to cite (and update Position accordingly).

### Counter-evidence I cannot dismiss
Bulleted list of case findings that DO NOT fit the leading hypothesis, or
alternatives whose pretest probability is genuinely competitive. You must
list these honestly. Skip the section if there is genuinely none.

### Confirming tests
Bulleted list of tests that would commit the leading hypothesis above
treatment threshold. Each entry: test name + LR+ (when known) + what it
confirms. Skip if the workup already confirmed the diagnosis or if no good
confirming test exists.

### Bottom line
ONE sentence summarizing your stance after this round.
```

Hard limit: ≤ 1500 words total. If you reach 1500, stop. The Judge prefers a
short, sharp defense over a long rambling one.

